SIMPLE: evanescent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Evanescent
<hw>Ev`a*nes"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>evanescens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>evanescere</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Liable to vanish or pass
away like vapor; vanishing; fleeting; <as>as, <ex>evanescent</ex>
joys</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>evanescent</qex> are the fashions of the world in these
particulars.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vanishing from notice; imperceptible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The difference between right and wrong, in some petty cases, is
almost <qex>evanescent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Wollaston.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evanescently</ent>⟦br⟧
